00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,440
right?

189
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,440
When it's not in equilibrium,

190
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,760
and then it comes to equilibrium,

191
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:11,620
generally speaking,

192
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:14,260
the probability distribution broadens.

193
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,400
We're going to prove that eventually.

194
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:21,700
We'll prove it in a qualitative kind of way.

195
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,000
Qualitatively,

196
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,640
we will prove the assertion that

197
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,280
if you have a probability distribution,

198
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:31,840
and you allow it to evolve,

199
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:36,159
being a little bit careless,

200
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:38,840
being a little bit careless,

201
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,440
being a little bit careless is called fine-graining,

202
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:42,480
coarse-graining,

203
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,179
excuse me,

204
00:08:43,179 --> 00:08:44,080
coarse-graining,

205
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:47,020
we'll find that the

206
00:08:47,020 --> 00:08:49,280
probability distribution always broadens.

207
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,360
And that's not surprising.

208
00:08:51,060 --> 00:08:53,680
For a probability distribution to narrow,

209
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:55,770
