00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,930
What happens is the energy just flows

289
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:03,960
from the hotter to the colder system

290
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:06,860
until they equilibrate.

291
00:12:07,020 --> 00:12:08,540
Until they equilibrate,

292
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:09,340
equilibrate,

293
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:10,100
as we will see,

294
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:13,400
means that the temperatures become equal.

295
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:16,780
When the temperatures on both sides become equal,

296
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:18,240
the heat stops flowing.

297
00:12:19,260 --> 00:12:21,000
That's kind of the meaning of temperature,

298
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:21,640
if you like.

299
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:24,220
The meaning of temperature is that

300
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:26,420
it tells you which way heat flows.

301
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:27,780
So number one,

302
00:12:27,780 --> 00:12:29,860
a notion of temperature exists

303
00:12:29,860 --> 00:12:32,200
such that heat flow,

304
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,320
energy flow,

305
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,800
is from the hotter to the colder.

306
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,340
When the temperatures become equal,

307
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,300
energy stops flowing.

308
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:45,000
And if A is in equilibrium with B,

309
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:47,050
that after all means that the temperature of

310
00:12:47,050 --> 00:12:48,840
A is the same as the temperature of B,

311
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,480
and B is in equilibrium with C,

312
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:53,850
that means that the temperature of B

313
00:12:53,850 --> 00:12:55,520
is equal to the temperature of C,

314
00:12:56,280 --> 00:13:00,640
then obviously A is in equilibrium with C.

315
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:02,280
That just says,

316
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,490
if the temperature of A is

317
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:04,700
the same as the temperature of B,

318
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:05,820
and the temperature of B is

319
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:06,860
the same as the temperature of C,

320
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,930
then the temperature of A and

321
00:13:08,930 --> 00:13:10,300
the temperature of C are the same.

322
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,220
So you can sort of summarize the,

323
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:15,400
you can summarize the zeroth law

324
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,440
by saying there's a notion of temperature,

325
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:18,840
which we've already introduced,

326
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:24,700
but we're going to use it to illuminate this law.

327
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,440
There's a notion of temperature,

328
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,040
number one.

329
00:13:29,220 --> 00:13:29,940
Number two,

330
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:34,680
energy flows from higher temperature to lower temperature,

331
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,620
and number three,

332
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,560
in thermal equilibrium,

333
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:40,480
the temperature of all parts

334
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,140
of the system is the same.

335
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:44,400
If the temperature was not the

336
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,060
same in all parts of the system,

337
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:47,520
energy would flow,

338
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:49,340
until it became the same.

339
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:51,820
That's the basic zeroth law.

340
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:54,220
The existence of a temperature function

341
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:57,060
that tells you which way energy flows,

342
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:59,920
and the existence of an equilibrium law,

343
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:01,400
when the temperature in all parts

344
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,860
of the system are the same.

345
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:03,620
Alright,

346
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:05,680
so let's see if we can relate that,

347
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,040
or those ideas,

348
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:09,560
to the notion of temperature,

349
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:13,120
that we introduced earlier,

350
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,200
last time,

351
00:14:14,340 --> 00:14:15,360
namely,

352
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:20,100
that temperature is related to the,

353
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,340
to the derivative of energy,

354
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:24,060
or the change in energy,

355
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,840
with respect to entropy.

356
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:31,440
If you change the energy a little bit,

357
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:33,180
the average energy,

358
00:14:33,180 --> 00:14:33,720
this means,

359
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:36,380
if you change the average energy a little bit,

360
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:38,340
the entropy will change,

361
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:40,940
and that derivative,

362
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:42,380
that rate of change,

363
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:43,900
is called the temperature.

364
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,050
Let's see if we can

365
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:49,580
see what this definition of temperature

366
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:52,350
has to do with the

367
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:55,120
idea of the flow of heat,

368
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,600
and which way it goes.

369
00:14:58,740 --> 00:14:59,260
So,

370
00:14:59,260 --> 00:14:59,960
let's begin,

371
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,840
let's take a two piece,

372
00:15:02,060 --> 00:15:04,080
a system composed of two parts,

373
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,860
let's call it A and B,

374
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:09,300
with a little pipe between them,

375
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:13,210
and let's write down all

376
00:15:13,210 --> 00:15:14,960
the basic equations that we know.

377
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,360
But before I start,

378
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:18,680
for the moment,

379
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:19,420
let's assume

380
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:23,200
that the temperature of B

381
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:26,160
is bigger than the temperature of A.

382
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:27,460
Now,

383
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:28,840
if the temperature of A

384
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,940
is bigger than the temperature of B,

385
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,020
just switch them.

386
00:15:32,839 --> 00:15:35,620
Just interchange A and B in everything I say.

387
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:36,940
Okay,

388
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:38,120
but we have to pick one.

389
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:39,740
Of course,

390
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:40,960
we could have the temperature of B

391
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,540
equal to the temperature of A,

392
00:15:42,620 --> 00:15:45,040
but let's take the case where they're not equal,

393
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:47,340
and that means they're not in equilibrium.

394
00:15:49,020 --> 00:15:50,140
They're not in equilibrium,

395
00:15:50,380 --> 00:15:51,470
the temperature of B is

396
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:52,560
bigger than the temperature of A.

397
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:53,480
Okay,

398
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,120
so let's write down some equations.

399
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,800
The first equation tells us

400
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:00,100
that when the system responds

401
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,620
and does whatever it's going to do,

402
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,880
the total energy doesn't change.

403
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:05,240
Now,

404
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:05,920
what is it going to do?

405
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:07,380
What it's going to do is

406
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:08,700
there's going to be some energy shift

407
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:09,880
from one to the other.

408
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:11,380
Alright,

409
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:14,220
so let's say the change in the energy of A

410
00:16:15,219 --> 00:16:17,660
plus the change in the energy of B

411
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,620
when whatever happens,

412
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:20,920
happens,

413
00:16:21,819 --> 00:16:22,640
in other words,

414
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:24,240
after a small amount of time,

415
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:26,900
that is equal to zero.

416
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,980
We take our stopwatch,

417
00:16:30,980 --> 00:16:32,220
we wait one second,

418
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:34,720
and we look how the energy redistributes itself.

419
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:37,560
We find out that the energy of A changes,

420
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,680
we find out that the energy of B changes,

421
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:42,820
but energy conservation tells us

422
00:16:42,820 --> 00:16:45,220
that the sum of the energies doesn't change.

423
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:47,900
Next,

424
00:16:50,620 --> 00:16:53,320
the change in the entropy of A

425
00:16:54,220 --> 00:16:57,060
plus the change in the entropy of B,

426
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,820
that's the change in the total entropy,

427
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:00,500
in fact,

428
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:04,319
that is always greater than,

429
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:06,579
once in a while it's equal to zero,

430
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,240
but only in very special cases,

431
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:10,619
the general statement is

432
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,980
that it's generally greater than zero.

433
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,440
The change in the entropy of A

434
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:18,480
plus the change in the entropy of B,

435
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:20,339
which is the change in the total entropy,

436
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,300
the entropy of the whole system,

437
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:25,520
in other words,

438
00:17:25,579 --> 00:17:29,300
the probability distribution of the combined system,

439
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:32,760
the probability distribution of the combined system

440
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:33,940
shifts in such a way

441
00:17:33,940 --> 00:17:37,140
as to make the distribution broader.

442
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:38,440
That's what it says.

443
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:40,600
Okay,

444
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:43,280
now let's use one more statement

445
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:46,020
that the change in the energy

446
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:51,700
is equal to the temperature

447
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:55,100
times the change in the entropy,

448
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,320
and let's apply this to both A and B.

449
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,120
DEA

450
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:04,720
is equal to the temperature of A

451
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:08,020
times the change of the entropy of A,

452
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:10,360
and same thing for B.

453
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:15,200
Then we can rewrite this equation over here,

454
00:18:15,340 --> 00:18:17,720
this is the first law of thermodynamics now,

455
00:18:18,580 --> 00:18:18,920
as

456
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:26,290
TA dS A plus TB

