00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:34,140
Or just to write it in a form

459
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:35,980
which is somewhat more useful for me,

460
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:40,700
I'm going to solve this equation for dS B.

461
00:18:42,740 --> 00:18:45,320
I'm going to solve it for this guy over here.

462
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,980
And what do we get?

463
00:18:50,220 --> 00:18:52,660
We get that dS B

464
00:18:58,940 --> 00:19:00,700
comma dS B

465
00:19:01,860 --> 00:19:03,480
is equal to minus,

466
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:07,520
because I'm going to transpose this term

467
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,700
to the right-hand side,

468
00:19:08,860 --> 00:19:09,740
that will give me a minus,

469
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:11,180
TA,

470
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:15,300
but now I have to divide by TA,

471
00:19:16,380 --> 00:19:20,060
minus TB dS A.

472
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:26,560
And now take this formula

473
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,640
and stick it into here.

474
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:31,240
You know,

475
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:31,780
as usual,

476
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:32,920
I always tell people,

477
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:33,660
to do physics,

478
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,580
you first think really hard

479
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:36,760
about what you want to do,

