547
00:22:10,660 --> 00:22:12,780
Let's just multiply this equation,

548
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:13,880
or this inequality,

549
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,820
by TA.

550
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:19,140
TA times dS A is bigger than zero.

551
00:22:19,260 --> 00:22:21,080
But what is TA times dS A?

552
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:25,720
It's the change in energy

553
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:27,760
of the subsystem A.

554
00:22:28,340 --> 00:22:31,960
This is d of the energy of A.

555
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:32,320
So,

556
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:33,100
what have we found?

557
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:35,020
By a little bit of manipulation,

558
00:22:35,780 --> 00:22:37,740
and the use of a couple of laws.

559
00:22:37,980 --> 00:22:38,760
What are the laws?

560
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,400
The first law,

561
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,440
energy conservation.

562
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:42,560
The second law,

563
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:43,800
entropy increases.

564
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:45,680
And that's all we used.

565
00:22:46,020 --> 00:22:47,600
Plus a little bit of juggling,

566
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,160
and transposing,

567
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:49,860
and multiplying

568
00:22:49,860 --> 00:22:52,340
by simple algebraic operations.

569
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:57,240
We find that the change in the energy of A

570
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:58,820
is greater than zero.

571
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:00,440
It follows,

572
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:01,060
of course,

573
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:03,000
that the change in the energy of B,

574
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:04,220
