00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:14,180
So we have proved,

580
00:23:14,719 --> 00:23:17,160
that with the definition of entropy,

581
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:19,720
sorry,

582
00:23:19,980 --> 00:23:21,840
the definition of temperature,

583
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:23,840
as given here,

584
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,400
that the temperature

585
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,380
is such,

586
00:23:30,740 --> 00:23:33,420
that it defines the direction of heat flow.

587
00:23:34,380 --> 00:23:35,440
Heat will flow,

588
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,640
and when I say heat,

589
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:37,240
incidentally,

590
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:37,720
I always,

591
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,860
I just mean energy.

592
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,140
Energy will flow from B to A,

593
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:44,720
until the temperatures become equal.

594
00:23:45,380 --> 00:23:47,040
When the temperatures become equal,

595
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:47,500
of course,

596
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:49,220
if T A equals T B,

597
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:50,180
then there's no flow.

598
00:23:50,260 --> 00:23:51,000
That's easy to see.

599
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:56,520
And that's when equilibrium is established.

600
00:23:56,900 --> 00:23:58,760
So equilibrium is established,

601
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:00,380
or there will be no flow of heat,

602
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:04,300
when T B equals T A,

603
00:24:05,639 --> 00:24:07,660
then there's no flow of heat altogether.

604
00:24:09,060 --> 00:24:09,540
Okay,

605
00:24:09,540 --> 00:24:10,780
so that's the,

606
00:24:12,379 --> 00:24:13,340
excuse me,

607
00:24:13,380 --> 00:24:15,280
the zeroth law of thermodynamics.

608
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:16,760
Namely,

609
00:24:16,780 --> 00:24:19,620
the temperature determines the direction of heat flow.

610
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:21,580
When the heat flow stops,

611
00:24:21,820 --> 00:24:23,400
because the system comes to equilibrium,

612
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:26,700
it must be that the temperature is the same

613
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:27,960
in every part of the system.

614
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:31,440
Conversely,

615
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,560
if the temperature is not the same

616
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,700
in every part of the system,

617
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,540
heat will flow until it is the same.

618
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:38,960
I have a question.

619
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:39,420
Yeah.

620
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:39,840
So,

621
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:40,920
it seems,

622
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:43,560
this analysis seems to assume that

623
00:24:44,879 --> 00:24:48,100
system A and system B individually are in equilibrium.

624
00:24:48,780 --> 00:24:49,260
Yeah,

625
00:24:49,260 --> 00:24:49,500
yeah,

626
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:49,620
yeah,

627
00:24:49,620 --> 00:24:50,600
that is true.

628
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:51,420
That is true.

629
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:52,280
That is true.

630
00:24:52,780 --> 00:24:54,540
But if they're not in equilibrium,

631
00:24:54,740 --> 00:24:56,860
it could be because when you break it up

632
00:24:56,860 --> 00:24:58,600
into smaller subsystems,

633
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,600
the smaller subsystems

634
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:03,040
are not in equilibrium with each other,

635
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:05,760
and then you just apply the analysis to the subsystems.

636
00:25:06,340 --> 00:25:06,880
Right.

637
00:25:08,660 --> 00:25:09,220
Good.

638
00:25:10,460 --> 00:25:11,020
Yeah,

639
00:25:11,020 --> 00:25:11,440
so,

640
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,840
that was correct.

641
00:25:13,060 --> 00:25:16,260
I did imagine that system A and system B

642
00:25:16,260 --> 00:25:17,800
separately were in equilibrium

643
00:25:18,660 --> 00:25:19,580
with themselves,

644
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:20,380
so to speak.

645
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,800
So that's a good point.

646
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:27,580
All right,

647
00:25:27,580 --> 00:25:28,980
now we come to the hard question.

648
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:30,240
Yeah.

649
00:25:31,260 --> 00:25:34,380
Just so I can have something specific in mind here,

650
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:35,800
when we talk about states,

651
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:38,520
should I think of this whole picture here

652
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:40,420
like we've got a gas in there,

653
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,240
should I think of the state as being

654
00:25:43,219 --> 00:25:45,520
the position and the velocity

655
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:49,120
or momentum of every single molecule in there?

656
00:25:49,260 --> 00:25:49,640
Yes,

657
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:51,380
except that in quantum mechanics

658
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:52,780
we can take those to be distinct.

659
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:53,380
Discrete variables,

660
00:25:53,380 --> 00:25:53,980
basically.

661
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,040
Yes,

662
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:55,900
that is.

663
00:25:56,020 --> 00:25:59,800
Or we simply substitute for S

664
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:03,060
an integral instead of a sum.

665
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:04,580
Yeah,

666
00:26:04,580 --> 00:26:05,400
but that's what,

667
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:05,720
yes.

668
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:07,080
Look,

669
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:09,460
a state always means the same thing.

670
00:26:09,620 --> 00:26:11,860
It means as much as you can possibly know

671
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:15,780
about the system if you were infinitely powerful.

672
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:19,480
Now,

673
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:25,320
there may be limits that have to do with

674
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:27,620
the fundamental rules of physics,

675
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:30,100
such as quantum mechanics,

676
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:32,440
which tells you you can't know as much

677
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,200
as you thought you might have liked to know,

678
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:36,740
such as the position and velocity of every particle.

679
00:26:37,020 --> 00:26:37,740
But still,

680
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:40,600
a state means as much as can be known

681
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:43,140
about a system

682
00:26:45,820 --> 00:26:46,380
by,

683
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:46,980
let's call it,

684
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:48,020
an infinitely powerful

685
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:49,460
observable system.

686
00:26:49,460 --> 00:26:50,020
Now,

687
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:51,980
there's a finite number of particles in there,

688
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:55,300
but their velocities and positions are not discrete.

689
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:56,600
In quantum mechanics,

690
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:57,120
they are.

691
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:58,400
Yeah.

692
00:26:58,520 --> 00:26:59,640
In quantum mechanics,

693
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:00,140
they are.

694
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:00,860
So,

695
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:03,320
in quantum mechanics,

696
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:06,740
the state counting for a finite box is discrete.

697
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:08,060
Yeah.

698
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,160
What we're going to have to show

699
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:18,260
is that if we do the correct quantum mechanics,

700
00:27:20,260 --> 00:27:21,340
statistical mechanics,

701
00:27:21,660 --> 00:27:23,020
then in a certain limit,

702
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:26,260
it becomes equal to the classical statistical mechanics.

703
00:27:26,540 --> 00:27:26,960
In other words,

704
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:27,760
in a certain limit,

705
00:27:27,940 --> 00:27:31,000
you can replace sums by integrals.

706
00:27:31,100 --> 00:27:32,320
That's what it comes down to.

707
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:34,200
And that's a subtle business.

708
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,820
That's not a one-liner.

709
00:27:36,980 --> 00:27:37,980
That's a subtle business,

710
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:38,960
but it is true.

711
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:41,900
All right.

712
00:27:41,940 --> 00:27:43,220
So now the next question,

713
00:27:43,220 --> 00:27:44,220
the open question,

714
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:46,780
is in equilibrium,

715
00:27:46,780 --> 00:27:48,880
after equilibrium is established,

716
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:53,020
you have this box of gas,

717
00:27:54,820 --> 00:27:56,040
or whatever it is,

718
00:27:56,860 --> 00:27:58,780
there's some probability distribution,

719
00:27:59,080 --> 00:27:59,920
P of I,

720
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,380
for the system to be in its different microstates.

721
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:08,280
What is that probability distribution?

722
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:11,580
What's the mathematics of it?

723
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,880
So that's what we're going to begin to study now.

724
00:28:16,780 --> 00:28:18,340
And right now...

725
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:29,000
First of all,

726
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:31,400
it's always a useful idea,

727
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:34,640
not only useful,

728
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:37,200
it usually corresponds to the facts,

729
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:41,680
to imagine that your system that you're interested in

730
00:28:42,500 --> 00:28:44,140
is not closed,

731
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,920
but is in contact

732
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:48,060
with the outside world

733
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:49,940
and can exchange energy with it.

734
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:51,140
In particular,

735
00:28:51,140 --> 00:28:52,440
it's a useful idea

736
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,360
if you want to think about

737
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:56,440
the probability distribution

738
00:28:56,440 --> 00:29:00,300
of the states of this subsystem,

739
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,800
to think of it as

740
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:05,100
being embedded in a huge reservoir

741
00:29:06,899 --> 00:29:10,380
of a much larger number of degrees of freedom

742
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:14,520
that provide a heat bath,

743
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,180
that provide a heat bath

744
00:29:17,180 --> 00:29:20,640
which allows energy to flow back and forth

745
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,980
until the system in question

746
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:30,360
comes to thermal equilibrium with the big heat bath.

747
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:33,160
The heat bath is so big

748
00:29:34,060 --> 00:29:36,800
that if even a little bit of energy flows

749
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:39,140
from into the subsystem,

750
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:41,300
the temperature doesn't change much.

751
00:29:41,500 --> 00:29:43,180
Now this is something we could also prove,

752
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:45,140
but just think about it for a minute.

753
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:46,700
We have a big,

754
00:29:46,700 --> 00:29:46,880
big,

755
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:47,100
big,

756
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:47,880
huge system

757
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,300
at a certain temperature,

758
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:51,140
and we have a little system,

759
00:29:51,140 --> 00:29:52,620
and a little bit of heat flows

760
00:29:52,620 --> 00:29:55,060
from the big system to the little system.

761
00:29:55,600 --> 00:29:56,120
Typically,

762
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:57,500
the change in the temperature

763
00:29:57,500 --> 00:30:01,160
of the big system will be negligible.

764
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:04,140
And so we can imagine the big system

765
00:30:04,140 --> 00:30:05,220
is at some temperature,

766
00:30:05,360 --> 00:30:08,040
and simply wait until the small system

767
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:11,360
is in equilibrium with the big system.

768
00:30:11,660 --> 00:30:13,160
Now a particularly important thing

769
00:30:13,180 --> 00:30:14,560
is that a particularly convenient choice

770
00:30:16,060 --> 00:30:17,200
of heat bath,

771
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:19,420
you'll see why,

772
00:30:20,780 --> 00:30:24,300
but a particularly convenient choice of heat bath,

773
00:30:24,980 --> 00:30:27,520
which often actually corresponds to the facts,

774
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:30,080
but a particularly interesting choice

775
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:31,440
is just to imagine

776
00:30:32,179 --> 00:30:33,600
that the system in question

777
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:38,900
is one of a very large number

778
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:41,240
of identical systems

779
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,460
which are connected together

780
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:46,220
by little pipes that allow heat

781
00:30:46,220 --> 00:30:47,240
to flow back and forth.

782
00:30:47,580 --> 00:30:49,960
One of them is the system

783
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:50,620
that we're studying,

784
00:30:50,820 --> 00:30:52,520
the rest of them simply provide

785
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:53,200
the heat bath.

786
00:30:57,240 --> 00:30:57,760
Actually,

787
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:59,000
this sometimes corresponds

788
00:30:59,000 --> 00:30:59,620
to the,

789
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:00,340
more or less,

790
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:00,740
the facts.

791
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:01,500
In particular,

792
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:04,300
if we have a very big system

793
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:06,240
and we divide it into small subsystems,

794
00:31:06,860 --> 00:31:09,380
the small subsystems may be very much alike,

795
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:11,220
and the big system then,

796
00:31:11,220 --> 00:31:12,280
is just the heat bath,

797
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,800
and the small subsystems

798
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:16,320
just provide a large number of replicas

799
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:18,720
that all together add up to the big system.

800
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:21,000
So this is a useful trick

801
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,060
