804
00:31:32,660 --> 00:31:34,600
How many such subsystems?

805
00:31:34,620 --> 00:31:35,120
Well,

806
00:31:35,120 --> 00:31:37,340
eventually we're going to let them get

807
00:31:37,340 --> 00:31:38,640
a large number of them,

808
00:31:38,740 --> 00:31:41,200
large enough that we can think of the heat bath

809
00:31:41,220 --> 00:31:41,900
as very big,

810
00:31:42,100 --> 00:31:44,940
but let's call it capital N for a moment.

811
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:47,440
That's the number of these systems we have.

812
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:50,620
And now each one of the systems

813
00:31:51,140 --> 00:31:52,660
is in a state.

814
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:54,320
Alright,

815
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:54,720
so I,

816
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,100
here's my demonstration.

817
00:32:00,420 --> 00:32:02,520
These are the identical systems.

818
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:06,020
What do I have?

819
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:06,240
One,

820
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:06,460
two,

821
00:32:06,460 --> 00:32:06,720
three,

822
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:07,100
four,

823
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:07,500
five,

824
00:32:07,500 --> 00:32:08,240
six,

825
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:08,920
seven,

826
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:09,460
eight,

827
00:32:09,460 --> 00:32:09,980
nine.

828
00:32:09,980 --> 00:32:12,460
So capital N is equal to nine.

829
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,280
These are the possible states.

830
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:21,200
These are all identical,

831
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:23,020
so I'm not going to do anything to them.

832
00:32:23,260 --> 00:32:25,380
But of course the states of the system

833
00:32:25,380 --> 00:32:26,220
are not identical.

834
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:27,820
They have different energy,

835
00:32:27,820 --> 00:32:28,480
for example.

836
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,160
So let's,

837
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:32,840
let's color them

838
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:33,860
to remind ourselves

839
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,740
that the states are not all alike.

840
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,140
And in particular,

841
00:32:40,140 --> 00:32:41,460
that they have different energy.

842
00:32:48,860 --> 00:32:50,580
The states are not real systems.

843
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,120
The states are just labels,

844
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:52,880
sort of.

845
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:52,980
Well,

846
00:32:52,980 --> 00:32:53,420
not labels,

847
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:53,880
but...

848
00:32:57,480 --> 00:32:58,960
And some of the systems

849
00:33:01,540 --> 00:33:03,900
are going to be in one state.

850
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:05,950
Some of them are going

851
00:33:05,950 --> 00:33:07,200
to be in the other state.

852
00:33:08,419 --> 00:33:10,880
And some of them will be in the third state.

853
00:33:10,980 --> 00:33:12,580
Here's a particularly simple example

854
00:33:12,580 --> 00:33:14,080
where there's only three states.

855
00:33:14,900 --> 00:33:16,800
Each state has different energy.

856
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:21,100
The energy might increase from right to left.

857
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,800
Your right to your left.

858
00:33:23,580 --> 00:33:24,220
No.

859
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:25,820
Your right...

860
00:33:26,719 --> 00:33:28,580
My right to my left.

861
00:33:28,820 --> 00:33:30,380
Your left to your...

862
00:33:31,060 --> 00:33:33,520
The energy increases in one direction.

863
00:33:35,259 --> 00:33:36,960
And what I want...

864
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:37,420
What...

865
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:37,680
What I want to do is...

866
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:42,240
I want to call the number of systems,

867
00:33:43,500 --> 00:33:44,060
subsystems,

868
00:33:44,060 --> 00:33:45,700
in the i-th state.

869
00:33:45,980 --> 00:33:46,540
Alright,

870
00:33:46,540 --> 00:33:47,340
here's the i-th state.

871
00:33:47,420 --> 00:33:48,220
Let's draw the states.

